{"cursor":"5169","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":".]] The 'President's Daily Brief' ('PDB'), sometimes referred to as\nthe 'President's Daily Briefing' or the 'President's Daily Bulletin', is a top-\nsecret document produced each morning for the President of the United States.\nResponsibility for producing the PDB — which was traditionally that of the\ndirector of the Central Intelligence Agency — was transferred to the\nDirector of National Intelligence on April 21, 2005, upon the confirmation of\nJohn Negroponte by the Senate. [http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A36532-\n2005Feb18.html CIA to Cede President's Brief to Negroponte], a February 19, 2005\n[[Washington Post]] article\n","linknr":156,"url":"President's_Daily_Brief","recorded":1362482892,"links":18,"instances":["united_states","cia_officer","information_gathering"],"pdf":["http://www.cnn.com/2004/images/04/10/whitehouse.pdf"],"categories":["Official documents of the United States","Central Intelligence Agency","Classified information in the United States","1960 establishments","Presidency of the United States"],"headings":["Purpose and history","Political importance","Public awareness","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/CIA_Memo.JPG/180px-CIA_Memo.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["intelligence","information_gathering"],["richard_lehman","cia_officer"],["national_security_advisor","united_states"]],"members":["national_security_advisor","richar